author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Apple’s AI rollout has been rocky, from Siri delays to underwhelming Apple Intelligence features. WSJ’s Joanna Stern sits down with software chief Craig Federighi and marketing head Greg Joswiak at WWDC 2025 in Cupertino to talk about the future of AI at Apple—and what the heck happened to that smarter Siri. 

Chapters:
0:00 WWDC 2025
0:22 Siri delays and struggles
3:49 Apple Intelligence struggles 
6:09 Apple’s AI future

Tech Things With Joanna Stern
Everything is now a tech thing. In creative and humorous videos, WSJ senior personal tech columnist Joanna Stern explains and reviews the products, services and trends that are changing our world.

#Apple #AI #WSJ
title: Apple Execs Defend Siri Delays, AI Plan and Apple Intelligence | WSJ

author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
As anti-ICE protests in L.A. continued for the fourth day in a row, WSJ’s Marc Vartabedian reported from the ground, following the action from the initial SEIU rally and then out into the streets as the protest evolved. For the first time in more than three decades, the Marines have been mobilized into a U.S. city to address civil unrest.

Chapters:
0:00 On the ground
0:20 Demonstration for David Huerta
2:27 U.S. military mobilizing Marines
3:03 Protests continue through downtown L.A.

#LA #Protests #WSJ
title: L.A. Protests: On the Ground as Trump Deploys Marines | WSJ

author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Your iPhone is about to look a lot different. Apple just announced iOS 26 at WWDC 2025, featuring a new “liquid glass” design and smarter calling tools including call screening, hold assist and live translation. WSJ’s Joanna Stern breaks down the biggest updates from Monday’s Worldwide Developers Conference at Apple Park in Cupertino.
